david vann reading events at stanford david vann reading facebook twitter email print add to calendar david vann is the author of legend of a suicide caribou island a mile down and last day on earth his work has been translated into 16 languages won a dozen prizes including the prix medicis in france and premi llibreter in spain been on 42 best books of the year lists worldwide selected by the new yorker book club and the times book club and serialized on north german radio and the bbc a current guggenheim fellow and former wallace stegner fellow john l heureux fellow and nea fellow he's a professor at the university of san francisco and has written for various magazines and newspapers in the us and uk www davidvann com when wednesday november 16 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where campbell recital hall braun music center map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags lecture reading humanities arts sponsor creative writing program contact 650 723 0011 krystalg stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 295 29533 more info last modified october 19 2011
